&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Third Wave Automation (TWA) is seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Technical Product Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to drive the tactical execution of our core robotic vehicle platforms. As we scale our strategic partnerships, you will be the &quot;boots on the ground&quot; responsible for managing the product lifecycle across our primary autonomous truck morphologies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will sit at the intersection of hardware and software, shepherding new vehicle requirements through engineering development and field trials. Your focus will be on ensuring our autonomous warehouse solutions meet rigorous market needs while facilitating the technical trade-offs necessary to hit our long-term scaling targets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How You Can Make an Impact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vehicle Morphology &amp;amp; Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Act as the &quot;Shepherd&quot; for living requirements for core trucks, facilitating critical trade-offs between engineering findings and initial product drafts during platform development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tactical Roadmap Execution:&lt;/strong&gt; Manage the backlog for the engineering team, utilizing technical project management tools to ensure high-velocity execution and alignment with the product roadmap.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Field Trial Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead vehicles through field trials, translating early adopter signals into actionable engineering tickets before product designs are finalized for mass production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deployed Fleet Management: &lt;/strong&gt;Oversee production uptime and resolve critical field issues for existing deployments while leveraging them as critical feedback sources for new features.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; 8+ years of experience in technical product management, specifically within&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;robotics, autonomous vehicles, or complex hardware-software integrated products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Proficiency:&lt;/strong&gt; Strong background in managing complex technical trade-off discussions and working directly with engineering teams to resolve hardware/software integration challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Execution Focus:&lt;/strong&gt; Exceptional skills in backlog grooming and project management; you should excel at translating high-level strategy into tactical &quot;boots on the ground&quot; execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adaptability:&lt;/strong&gt; Ability to thrive in a fast-paced environment where engineering findings frequently require rapid pivots in product requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication:&lt;/strong&gt; Strong ability to translate field signals and customer feedback into clear, prioritized technical requirements for development teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
